  3.9465319639586086`*^9},ExpressionUUID->"f0657414-5c4f-446d-8541-\
f905c6551be5"]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Note that the number of neurons is the same in the three networks. \n\n\
Train the three ANNs using the data created in Task 1. Compare the \
predictions of each trained ANN with ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  FormBox[
   RowBox[{"f", "(", "x", ")"}], TraditionalForm]],ExpressionUUID->
  "8c0f9a7e-556c-4857-bbc8-722709d3a890"],
 ". Discuss the results. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.8210272488990374`*^9, 3.8210273301895423`*^9}, {
   3.8210275161291437`*^9, 3.821027624763609*^9}, {3.8210276765901794`*^9, 
   3.821027684892828*^9}, {3.8210278112661743`*^9, 3.8210278114576635`*^9}, {
   3.821027846060079*^9, 3.821027876437887*^9}, 3.82169080528373*^9, 
   3.82169101817485*^9},ExpressionUUID->"1700717c-ac8c-4201-8f20-\
c680395003ea"]
}, Open  ]]
}, Open  ]],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Exercise 2. Class net encoder for logistic regression for nominal classes\
\>", "Section",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.825943262936699*^9, 
  3.8259433136275096`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"3f158801-9c9a-4bd4-80a7-\
88fa324fa723"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "This exercise is related to the ANN for logistic regression presented in \
the lectures notebook Ch8-1 (section \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Understanding \
ANNs through simple examples). Consider, in particular, the simple ANN called \
",
 StyleBox["logistic2", "CodeText"],
 " in Ch8-1. The output variable of the ANN ",
 StyleBox["logistic2", "CodeText"],
 "  was numeric even if logistic regression is a method that can be used for \
classification to any class that does not need to be numeric. In order to  \
consider a genuine nominal variable corresponding to, e.g., two classes A and \
B, one needs to add a \[OpenCurlyDoubleQuote]Class\[CloseCurlyDoubleQuote] \
net encoder (see Ch8-2_ML_NeuralNetworks_PartII.nb) to the ANN ",
 StyleBox["logistic2", "CodeText"],
 " defined in lectures. In addition, we append a ",
 StyleBox["SoftmaxLayer[]", "CodeText"],
 " which normalizes the output of the ",
 StyleBox["logistic2", "CodeText"],
 " ANN in order to use it as class probabilities for classification tasks. "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.819896876133521*^9, 3.819897046955512*^9}, {
   3.8198972041827507`*^9, 3.819897235578994*^9}, {3.8198974033578625`*^9, 
   3.8198974575092363`*^9}, {3.819897563090469*^9, 3.819897613871565*^9}, 
   3.8198976787744913`*^9, {3.819897780718637*^9, 3.8198977811893835`*^9}, {
   3.8198980062375097`*^9, 3.8198980947047663`*^9}, {3.8198982944701557`*^9, 
   3.8198984652266483`*^9}, {3.825943598244012*^9, 3.8259437861710997`*^9}, {
   3.825943853696606*^9, 3.8259438806809587`*^9}, {3.8259439222005053`*^9, 
   3.825943922361038*^9}, {3.825945464638895*^9, 3.825945465754265*^9}, {
   3.8259455008456383`*^9, 3.8259455030228863`*^9}, {3.8259456884584107`*^9, 
   3.8259456919311023`*^9}, {3.825945889164298*^9, 3.8259458957747383`*^9}, {
   3.8259459990852013`*^9, 3.8259461636604567`*^9}, {3.825946203496251*^9, 
   3.825946243907368*^9}, {3.8259462900626755`*^9, 3.8259463008872175`*^9}, {
   3.825946354362159*^9, 3.825946443734376*^9}, 
